1 B. As used in this act the Oklahoma National Guard Educational
2 Assistance Act:
3 1. “Oklahoma educational institution” means an institution of
4 higher education within The Oklahoma State System of Higher
5 Education;
6 2. “Eligible Guard member” means a current member of the
7 Oklahoma National Guard in good standing who has a high school
8 diploma or who has completed General Educational Development (GED)
9 requirements and who has secured admission to and enrolled in an
10 Oklahoma educational institution;
11 3. “Graduate program” means a program offered by an Oklahoma
12 educational institution that leads to the award of a master’s
13 degree;
14 4. “Program” means the Oklahoma National Guard Educational
15 Assistance Program established pursuant to the provisions of this
16 section; and
17 5. “Undergraduate program” means a program offered by an
18 Oklahoma educational institution that leads to the award of an
19 associate’s degree or a baccalaureate degree.
20 C. There is hereby created the Oklahoma National Guard
21 Educational Assistance Program to provide assistance to eligible
22 Guard members who enroll in an Oklahoma educational institution.
23 Subject to the availability of funds and limitations established by
24 the Oklahoma State Regents for Higher Education, the amount of
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - SB32 SFLR Page 2
