1 assi stance shall be equivalent to the amount of resident tuition,
2 mandatory fees, and program fees, academic service fees, and any
3 other fees for courses in which the eligible Guard member is
4 enrolled, not to exceed a maximum of eighteen (18) credit hours each
5 semester. The mandatory fees, program fees, academic service fees,
6 and any other fees for courses shall be jointly reviewed by the
7 State Regents and the Military Department of the State of Oklahoma.
8 The State Regents may determine fees or fee amounts to be ineligible
9 for program assistance. If the State Regents make such a
10 determination, program assistance for those fees or fee amounts
11 shall not be provided to eligible Guard members participating in the
12 program.
13 1. The amount of assistance provided to an eligible Guard
14 member enrolled in an undergraduate program shall not exceed a
15 maximum of one hundred twenty (120) credit hours in pursuit of an
16 associate’s degree and/or a baccalaureate degree.
17 2. Subject to the assistance for eligible Guard members
18 enrolled in undergraduate programs being fully funded, assistance
19 shall be provided to an eligible Guard member with a baccalaureate
20 degree enrolled in a graduate program. The amount of assistance
21 provided to an eligible Guard member enrolled in a graduate program
22 shall not exceed a maximum of forty (40) credit hours in pursuit of
23 a master’s degree.
24
