1 H. The eligible Guard member’s Commander may deny an
2 application submitted by an eligible Guard member for continued
3 Program program assistance if he or she fails to comply with the
4 provisions of paragraph 1, 2, or 3, 4, or 5 of subsection F of this
5 section.
6 I. An eligible Guard member who has received Program program
7 assistance pursuant to the provisions of this section and who fails
8 to comply with the provisions of paragraph 4 of subsection F of this
9 section shall be required to repay an amount to be calculated as
10 follows:
11 1. Determine the total amount of assistance provided pursuant
12 to the provisions of this section;
13 2. Divide the amount determined in paragraph 1 of this
14 subsection by twenty-four (24); and
15 3. Multiply the amount determined in paragraph 2 of this
16 subsection by the number of months the member did not fulfill the
17 requirements of paragraph 4 of subsection F of this section.
18 Repayments shall be deposited into the Oklahoma National Guard
19 Educational Assistance Revolving Fund created pursuant to Section 2
20 3232 of this act title.
21 J. An eligible Guard member who has received Program program
22 assistance pursuant to the provisions of this section and who fails
23 to comply with the provisions of paragraph 4 of subsection F of this
24 section due to hardship circumstances may request a waiver from
